The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, February 07, 2004  Good Morning Hello It's Saturday, February 7, 2004				 																What to do this weekend				 																																	Hear British author and wildlife filmmaker Nick Gordon speak on Secret Life of the Jaguar, Calcutta Book Fair, 5.45 pm.				 																Awareness fair				 																																	Drop in at the Disabled Day awareness mela, entitled Children of the Same God, at Triangular Park, from 1 pm to 7 pm. The fair will be inaugurated at 4 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	Visit an exhibition of new works by Chittrovanu Mazumdar at Uma, 2/4A Sarat Bose Road, from 2 pm to 8 pm.				 																																	Catch the annual art exhibition, Calcutta Painters, at the Academy of Fine Arts, from 3 pm to 8 pm. The works of 12 artists are on display.				 																Talent finale				 																																	Cheer the young participants at the grand finale of the Kidzee Talent Hunt, at Bharatiyam Cultural Complex, Salt Lake, from 3 pm.
